data.title: Arch Lifts
data.information: Arch Lifts increase resilience in the tendon in the arch of the foot. A sedentary lifestyle weakens your feet, which is why it’s important to train them in order to prevent injuries.

data.title: Ballerina
data.information: Ballerina improves flexibility in your big toe. Reduced big toe flexibility can cause pain in the arch of your foot, which is why it is important to restore and maintain good joint mobility in your big toe.

data.title: Big Toe Extension against a door frame
data.app_title: Big Toe Extension \nAgainst a Door Frame \n(2 sets)
data.information: Big Toe Extension against a door frame improves flexibility in your big toe. Reduced big toe flexibility can cause pain in the arch of your foot, which is why it is important to restore and maintain good joint mobility in your big toe. Big toe flexibility is also important for walking.

data.title: Seated Arch Stretch
data.information: Seated Arch Stretch stretches the tendon in the arch of your foot. Pain in the arch of the foot causes the tendon to contract and tighten. The stretch restores flexibility and prevents recurring discomfort.

data.title: Standing Toe Piano
data.information: Standing Toe Piano strengthens your feet, improves resilience and reduces the risk of recurring discomfort. Performing the exercise standing increases the strain, which further strengthens your feet.

data.title: Towel Roll
data.information: Towel Roll strengthens the muscles in your feet, increasing tolerance and resilience.
